The changing landscape of work and careers. The psychological contract between employees and employers. What is a career? The career management process. 
Traditional perspectives on careers. Social influences on careers. The different meanings of career success. Stages of career development. 
Work-life balance. Work-life conflict. Societal responses to the work-life conflict (incl. organisations). Work-life decision-making process. 
Model of career management. Indicators of effective career management. 
Application of the career management model - goals of self-exploration, career goal setting, strategies. 
Choosing a suitable occupation and organisation. Preferred work environment.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of the course is to provide students with an integrative approach to managing their careers to achieve a satisfying balance between their work and family life responsibilities, community involvement, and personal interests. The career management model explored in the course guides individuals through the different phases of their career.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) knows how to maintain work-life balance; 2) knows the contemporary approach to the career context and stages; 3) knows and be able to apply the career management model; 4) is aware of his/her preferred work environment and organisation.
